description: Natalie "Tally" Nourigat is a cartoonist from Portland, Oregon. You may know her from Between Gears (Image), It Girl! and the Atomics, A Boy and a Girl, or her current webcomic Home is Where the Internet Is. Natalie loves traveling, meeting new people, and drawing late into the night. She is currently living in Paris and exploring other parts of Europe whenever possible.
name: Natalie Nourigat

deck: Louis Little was a cartoonist from Halifax, Nova Scotia. He drew the science fiction series "3 to Infinity" during the nineties.
name: Louis Little

deck: Nick Firfires was an artist whose works usually had a Western theme. He drew for many Western comics during the Golden Age.
description: Firfires was the son-in-law of Buck Jones, a Western star during the 1930s and early 40s who was featured in many of the comics Firfires worked on.
name: Nicholas Firfires

deck: Monique Renee (MacNaughton) is a comic artist. Her two creations U.N.A. Frontiers and Arrowflight are published by Coydog Press.
name: Monique Renee

deck: Artist on mystery and romance comics during the Golden Age. He is most famous for drawing numerous issues of Shadow Comics.
description: Greene worked with Street and Smith and Dell Comics, as well as on syndicated comic strips.

deck: British cartoonist and comic scriptwriter Andy Riley is best known for the Bunny Suicides comic strips. He has also worked for television and, along with friend Kevin Cecil, won a BAFTA for his contribution to the Comic Relief TV special Robbie The Reindeer.
name: Andy Riley
